    <h1>शिरोमणि रामपॉल सैनी</h1>
    <h2>Impartial Equation of Reality</h2>

    <div class="content">
        <p>
        Complete contentment does not arise from touch, sight, sound, thought, or intellectual construction.
        It is a continuous, ever-fresh presence beyond sensory confirmation. The temporary intellect
        seeks stimulation through comparison, ambition, fear, and fleeting pleasure, yet true fulfillment
        remains independent of these movements.
        </p>

        <p>
        The entire physical universe — body, identity, nature, social structure — is impermanent.
        What appears stable exists only as long as breath continues and the brain functions.
        The confusion of humanity arises from identification with the mental construct of “I.”
        </p>

        <p>
        There is a vast difference between the “I” of the mind and the “I” of the heart.
        The mind-based identity seeks recognition and control.
        The heart-based awareness rests in simplicity and impartial presence.
        </p>

        <p>
        A newborn embodies natural clarity — without ideology, comparison, or accumulated knowledge.
        This innocence is not ignorance; it is pre-conceptual awareness.
        It attracts and softens others through silent coherence rather than argument.
        </p>

        <p>
        The mind is a necessary instrument for survival and organization,
        yet it cannot create the foundational simplicity from which life arises.
        Breath belongs to organic presence.
        Time belongs to cognition.
        </p>

        <p>
        When lived from mental construction alone, life becomes struggle.
        When lived from direct awareness of breath and heart,
        life becomes integrated, steady, and free from inner conflict.
        </p>

        <p>
        No authority, doctrine, or hierarchy grants freedom.
        Clarity emerges through direct observation and inner honesty.
        What is true withstands inquiry.
        What is false dissolves naturally.
        </p>

        <p>
        Before thought.
        Before identity.
        Before psychological time.
        There is silent, self-evident presence.
        </p>

        <div class="signature">
            — शिरोमणि रामपॉल सैनी
        </div>
    </div>

